## Purpose

Create cross-language lint parity tests that verify equivalent code patterns produce equivalent lint results across TypeScript, Go, and Python. This ensures the 21 rules behave consistently regardless of which language implementation is running. The tests do NOT run the actual lint tools — they verify that the same conceptual violation triggers the same rule in each language by running each language's checker/analyzer on equivalent bad code.

## Spec References

- `specs/rules/lint-rules.md` — Rule Catalog (all 21 rules with language applicability)
- `specs/rules/lint-rules.md` — RULE-08 (no-async-noise) is TS only
- `specs/rules/lint-rules.md` — TEST-05 (no-snapshot-only-tests) is TS only
- `specs/rules/lint-rules.md` — STRUCT-07 (filename-match-export) does not apply to Go (D-30)
- `specs/rules/lint-rules.md` — STRUCT-01/02 are config-driven for TS/Go, custom checker for Python only (D-36)
- `specs/rules/lint-rules.md` — Cross-Language Parity Tests section under Testing Strategy

